CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper October 27, 1945, pg. 9, reads: "Juggler - The small fry will have a prominent part in the Beauty Shop Owners' Big Charity Show, Thursday night, Oct. 25, in Schenley High School Auditorium. David Dorgan, a newcomer in public life, is all set to 'show 'em' how juggling is done. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of boy juggler David Dorgan wearing Spanish style costume and holding maracas, posed in front of dark curtain in Harris Studio
